Oh, Junhui?

240
00:14:55,090 --> 00:14:56,420
Hi, Yeonhui.

241
00:14:56,430 --> 00:14:57,790
Yeongeun, can you get us some coffee?

242
00:14:57,790 --> 00:14:58,860
Okay.

243
00:15:00,300 --> 00:15:02,800
What's up? You didn't go to work?

244
00:15:02,800 --> 00:15:05,700
No, I wanted to see you first.

245
00:15:05,700 --> 00:15:07,200
You should've told me in advance.

246
00:15:07,200 --> 00:15:09,370
I would've come to work earlier.

247
00:15:09,370 --> 00:15:10,840
I just got here.

248
00:15:12,240 --> 00:15:13,670
Enjoy your coffee.

249
00:15:14,880 --> 00:15:17,650
But what are you doing here so early?

250
00:15:19,480 --> 00:15:21,750
Yeonhui.

251
00:15:21,750 --> 00:15:23,580
What is the nature of

252
00:15:23,590 --> 00:15:26,190
your relationship with Yu Seongbin?

253
00:15:26,190 --> 00:15:29,060
What do you mean by that?

254
00:15:29,060 --> 00:15:32,460
I saw you yesterday when you came

255
00:15:32,460 --> 00:15:34,930
to our workplace, driving off with him.

256
00:15:36,100 --> 00:15:38,670
Seongbin and I had a dinner appointment.

257
00:15:38,670 --> 00:15:40,200
Without a single apology,

258
00:15:40,200 --> 00:15:42,700
he cancelled our dinner to go with you.

259
00:15:42,700 --> 00:15:44,740
Do you know how upset I was?

260
00:15:44,740 --> 00:15:46,640
Junhui, that's because...

261
00:15:46,640 --> 00:15:51,250
I know that Seongbin had liked you

262
00:15:51,250 --> 00:15:53,480
for a long time.

263
00:15:53,480 --> 00:15:56,050
And I was relieved it wasn't so anymore.

264
00:15:56,050 --> 00:15:58,150
But now I discover that it was you,

265
00:15:58,150 --> 00:16:00,590
not Seongbin, who is to blame.

266
00:16:00,590 --> 00:16:03,890
Why did you pick Seongbin up from work?

267
00:16:03,890 --> 00:16:05,630
Why did you do that?

268
00:16:05,630 --> 00:16:07,860
Do you like Seongbin?

269
00:16:07,900 --> 00:16:09,430
Do you love him?

270
00:16:10,400 --> 00:16:12,330
Have you forgotten that

271
00:16:12,330 --> 00:16:13,830
you're a married woman?

272
00:16:13,840 --> 00:16:17,240
Junhui, how can you say that?

273
00:16:17,240 --> 00:16:21,940
I've been keeping quiet because of my pride

274
00:16:21,940 --> 00:16:24,110
but I like Seongbin.

275
00:16:24,110 --> 00:16:25,550
No, I love him.

276
00:16:27,020 --> 00:16:28,780
That's why I want to marry him.

277
00:16:28,780 --> 00:16:33,320
So from now on, try not to come between us.

278
00:16:34,090 --> 00:16:35,590
That's what I came to tell you.

279
00:16:36,160 --> 00:16:37,160
Junhui!

280
00:16:38,090 --> 00:16:39,260
Junhui!

281
00:16:39,960 --> 00:16:42,130
Junhui, hear me out, will you?

282
00:16:42,130 --> 00:16:44,330
How can you leave like this?

283
00:16:45,270 --> 00:16:47,200
Seongbin and I

284
00:16:47,200 --> 00:16:49,700
have been friends since college.

285
00:16:49,700 --> 00:16:51,740
But you know this already.

286
00:16:51,740 --> 00:16:53,770
There's nothing going on between us.

287
00:16:53,780 --> 00:16:56,140
How can you take it that way?

288
00:16:56,140 --> 00:16:58,750
Is that what you think of me?

289
00:16:58,750 --> 00:17:00,750
Don't come between the two of you?

290
00:17:00,750 --> 00:17:02,880
Are you saying that I'm having an affair

291
00:17:02,880 --> 00:17:05,050
when I have my husband and Jinwu?

292
00:17:06,660 --> 00:17:08,420
I'm sorry.

293
00:17:08,420 --> 00:17:11,290
But Seongbin only cares about you.

294
00:17:12,090 --> 00:17:15,360
He just feels sorry for me.

295
00:17:15,360 --> 00:17:17,900
Because I've always been such a fool.

296
00:17:17,900 --> 00:17:20,100
You say the same thing.

297
00:17:20,100 --> 00:17:22,700
You call me foolish and clumsy.

298
00:17:22,700 --> 00:17:24,410
When did I say that?

299
00:17:31,480 --> 00:17:33,880
Never mind. Give me my coffee.

300
00:17:33,880 --> 00:17:35,780
I might as well finish it, as long as I'm here.

301
00:17:35,780 --> 00:17:37,420
I want you to pay for it.

302
00:17:37,420 --> 00:17:39,420
I can't offer it for free all the time.

303
00:17:39,420 --> 00:17:41,220
I don't make a lot of money.

304
00:17:44,730 --> 00:17:46,730
A professional dry cleaning

305
00:17:46,730 --> 00:17:48,260
service washed them.

306
00:17:48,260 --> 00:17:51,600
But there still were stains on the napkins?

307
00:17:51,600 --> 00:17:53,130
Yes, ma'am.

308
00:17:53,130 --> 00:17:57,270
That's why I adamantly filed a complaint.

309
00:17:58,610 --> 00:18:00,070
This won't do.

310
00:18:00,080 --> 00:18:02,540
Let's look for another dry cleaning service.

311
00:18:02,540 --> 00:18:04,350
Yes, ma'am.

312
00:18:04,450 --> 00:18:05,910
And Chef Bae?

313
00:18:05,910 --> 00:18:08,020
I know what you're going to say.

314
00:18:08,020 --> 00:18:09,750
I'm glad to hear that.

315
00:18:09,750 --> 00:18:11,950
Don't forget to wear your chef bandana.

316
00:18:11,950 --> 00:18:13,820
It's right here.

317
00:18:13,820 --> 00:18:15,850
And cut your hair short.

318
00:18:16,490 --> 00:18:17,720
I already had it trimmed.

319
00:18:17,730 --> 00:18:19,540
A bit shorter.

320
00:18:20,160 --> 00:18:22,400
I can't cut it any shorter.

321
00:18:22,560 --> 00:18:25,630
Why not? You can trim it a bit shorter.

322
00:18:26,640 --> 00:18:30,470
Are you telling me to shave it bald?

323
00:18:30,470 --> 00:18:32,870
I'm not saying that.

324
00:18:32,870 --> 00:18:35,480
Fine, that would be even better.

325
00:18:35,480 --> 00:18:37,440
Are you telling me to become a monk?

326
00:18:37,450 --> 00:18:38,910
What?

327
00:18:38,910 --> 00:18:41,880
Why would I cut my hair like a monk?

328
00:18:41,880 --> 00:18:45,050
Are you playing with me here?

329
00:18:45,050 --> 00:18:47,960
You want to play around? Fine then.

330
00:18:47,960 --> 00:18:49,860
What? Gosh!

331
00:18:51,590 --> 00:18:52,790
My goodness!

332
00:18:55,960 --> 00:18:58,370
Why did you do that?

333
00:18:58,370 --> 00:18:59,630
What?

334
00:19:00,940 --> 00:19:02,170
Cheese!

335
00:19:03,170 --> 00:19:04,540
Whiskey!

336
00:19:08,640 --> 00:19:10,010
Chansik.

337
00:19:10,010 --> 00:19:13,410
No, I mean Chef Michael.

338
00:19:13,420 --> 00:19:15,280
What's wrong with you today?

339
00:19:15,280 --> 00:19:18,850
Ms. Jeong is in a bad mood.

340
00:19:18,850 --> 00:19:21,220
I'm in a worse mood.

341
00:19:21,220 --> 00:19:23,090
Worse, worse, worse!

342
00:19:24,090 --> 00:19:25,630
What?

343
00:19:26,530 --> 00:19:28,900
What's wrong with the two of them?

344
00:19:33,230 --> 00:19:35,000
I just can't believe him.

345
00:19:35,000 --> 00:19:36,800
Unbelievable!

346
00:19:36,810 --> 00:19:39,140
He must be crazy. Crazy!

347
00:19:41,340 --> 00:19:43,240
I have an awful headache.

348
00:19:44,380 --> 00:19:45,510
Come in.

349
00:19:54,560 --> 00:19:56,520
This is Dutch coffee.

350
00:19:57,760 --> 00:19:59,060
What is this for?

351
00:19:59,060 --> 00:20:01,500
I didn't ask for any coffee.

352
00:20:01,500 --> 00:20:03,500
For 24 hours,

353
00:20:03,500 --> 00:20:07,270
vapors formed drop by drop to create it.

354
00:20:07,270 --> 00:20:08,440
So?

355
00:20:08,440 --> 00:20:10,600
I know you're in a bad mood right now.

356
00:20:10,610 --> 00:20:12,610
A very bad mood.

357
00:20:12,610 --> 00:20:16,080
No, you're feeling worse than that.

358
00:20:16,080 --> 00:20:18,880
So I hope the coffee will comfort you.

359
00:20:18,880 --> 00:20:21,720
Ms. Lee, what's wrong with you?

360
00:20:21,720 --> 00:20:22,950
Are you playing with me?

361
00:20:22,950 --> 00:20:24,890
What's wrong with everyone today?

362
00:20:24,890 --> 00:20:27,150
I'm sorry.

363
00:20:27,160 --> 00:20:28,360
Wait.

364
00:20:28,960 --> 00:20:31,360
Did you get in touch with Lee Hwayeong?

365
00:20:31,360 --> 00:20:33,430
No, not yet.

366
00:20:33,430 --> 00:20:34,900
Okay, you may leave.

367
00:20:34,900 --> 00:20:36,830
Yes, ma'am.

368
00:20:40,370 --> 00:20:41,940
Gosh.

369
00:20:44,170 --> 00:20:47,140
If she finishes up the contract and leaves

370
00:20:47,140 --> 00:20:49,110
for New York, all would be well.

371
00:20:49,110 --> 00:20:51,380
I'm in a bad enough mood to begin with!

372
00:20:51,380 --> 00:20:54,410
Why is that chef making me even more upset?

373
00:20:54,420 --> 00:20:55,820
Geez!

374
00:21:07,260 --> 00:21:10,160
Ms. Baek, are you okay?

375
00:21:10,170 --> 00:21:13,070
Yes, I'm fine.

376
00:21:13,070 --> 00:21:14,030
I'll clean it up.

377
00:21:14,040 --> 00:21:16,470
- Yeongeun?
- Yes?

378
00:21:16,470 --> 00:21:20,170
Do you know Grace Lee?

379
00:21:20,180 --> 00:21:22,210
Have you heard of her?

380
00:21:22,210 --> 00:21:25,380
Grace Lee? I do know her.

381
00:21:25,380 --> 00:21:26,850
You do?

382
00:21:26,850 --> 00:21:28,720
How do you know her?

383
00:21:28,720 --> 00:21:31,220
She's a regular customer here.

384
00:21:31,220 --> 00:21:33,550
And you two are really close.

385
00:21:33,560 --> 00:21:35,620
We're close?

386
00:21:35,620 --> 00:21:37,420
Who is it?

387
00:21:37,430 --> 00:21:39,130
The person from America.

388
00:21:39,960 --> 00:21:41,760
Hwayeong?

389
00:21:42,400 --> 00:21:45,400
Hwayeong is Grace Lee?

390
00:21:45,400 --> 00:21:47,730
Yes, it's her American name.

391
00:21:48,340 --> 00:21:51,310
Are you sure about this?

392
00:21:52,070 --> 00:21:53,740
I'm pretty sure.

393
00:21:56,280 --> 00:21:58,650
<i>Do you know a woman named Grace Lee?</i>

394
00:21:58,650 --> 00:22:01,580
<i>Your husband, Jeong Byeongguk,</i>

395
00:22:01,580 --> 00:22:03,920
<i>is rumored to be having an affair with her.</i>

396
00:22:05,350 --> 00:22:06,450
Oh.

397
00:22:09,390 --> 00:22:10,690
How do you do?

398
00:22:10,690 --> 00:22:12,130
Hello.

399
00:22:12,630 --> 00:22:14,060
I didn't know I'd run into

400
00:22:14,060 --> 00:22:15,930
your husband like this.

401
00:22:15,930 --> 00:22:17,930
He's so handsome.

402
00:22:17,930 --> 00:22:21,470
You should be on guard always.

403
00:22:21,470 --> 00:22:22,470
Why?

404
00:22:22,470 --> 00:22:24,200
What if someone were to

405
00:22:24,210 --> 00:22:25,770
take him away from you?

406
00:22:25,770 --> 00:22:27,640
Even I want to steal him away.

407
00:22:30,010 --> 00:22:32,610
Ms. Baek!

408
00:22:34,550 --> 00:22:36,950
I think she put in a good word

409
00:22:36,950 --> 00:22:38,990
about us to Lasar's main office.

410
00:22:38,990 --> 00:22:40,320
They're nearly done looking over it.

411
00:22:40,320 --> 00:22:42,190
Only the final decision is left.

412
00:22:42,190 --> 00:22:43,620
That's a relief.

413
00:22:43,630 --> 00:22:46,830
We've been working on this for seven years.

414
00:22:50,230 --> 00:22:52,300
Mr. Jeong, the madam is here to see you.

415
00:22:52,300 --> 00:22:54,640
Who are you talking about?

416
00:22:54,640 --> 00:22:57,070
Your wife is here.

417
00:22:57,070 --> 00:22:58,670
My wife?

418
00:23:01,210 --> 00:23:02,640
Honey?

419
00:23:02,670 --> 00:23:05,050
- Hi.
- Oh, hey.

420
00:23:05,410 --> 00:23:08,280
What are you doing here?

421
00:23:08,280 --> 00:23:11,220
I have something to ask you.

422
00:23:11,220 --> 00:23:14,120
I'll leave you two to talk.

423
00:23:17,160 --> 00:23:20,190
You said you wouldn't come here.

424
00:23:20,190 --> 00:23:21,560
With the coffee shop close by,

425
00:23:21,560 --> 00:23:23,660
it won't do us any good if you're

426
00:23:23,670 --> 00:23:25,200
always paying me a visit.

427
00:23:26,030 --> 00:23:29,070
So Grace Lee is Lee Hwayeong?

428
00:23:29,070 --> 00:23:30,870
Why didn't you tell me?

429
00:23:30,870 --> 00:23:32,040
Huh?

430
00:23:32,970 --> 00:23:35,680
Oh, I didn't?

431
00:23:35,680 --> 00:23:38,510
I didn't think I had to.

432
00:23:38,510 --> 00:23:40,210
We even had dinner together.

433
00:23:40,210 --> 00:23:42,050
Why didn't you say anything then?

434
00:23:42,050 --> 00:23:43,820
That's because...

435
00:23:45,020 --> 00:23:47,220
Wait. Did you come all the way

436
00:23:47,220 --> 00:23:48,990
here to ask me that?

437
00:23:48,990 --> 00:23:51,390
It's not such a big deal.

438
00:23:51,390 --> 00:23:52,730
Honey.

439
00:23:54,500 --> 00:23:55,630
What?

440
00:23:55,630 --> 00:23:58,300
<i>Mr. Kwon from Arabesque is on the phone.</i>

441
00:23:58,300 --> 00:23:59,600
Put him through.

442
00:24:02,770 --> 00:24:05,840
Hello, Mr. Kwon. This is Byeongguk.

443
00:24:07,380 --> 00:24:08,510
Yes.

444
00:24:27,130 --> 00:24:29,260
<i>The person you are trying to reach is not...</i>

445
00:24:34,770 --> 00:24:36,940
My boyfriend gave it to me.

446
00:24:42,410 --> 00:24:44,710
Oh, hello! How are you?

447
00:24:44,710 --> 00:24:46,110
Hello.

448
00:24:46,110 --> 00:24:48,950
I guess you're here to meet your husband.

449
00:24:48,950 --> 00:24:50,080
Bye now!

450
00:24:54,060 --> 00:24:58,360
She doesn't look so well.

451
00:24:58,360 --> 00:25:00,930
Maybe she found out about the affair.

452
00:25:00,930 --> 00:25:02,860
Watch what you say!

453
00:25:02,860 --> 00:25:04,770
You don't know the truth.

454
00:25:05,530 --> 00:25:08,270
You should look after your daughter.

455
00:25:08,270 --> 00:25:10,800
Your daughter will end up in hell that way.

456
00:25:10,810 --> 00:25:11,770
What?

457
00:25:11,770 --> 00:25:14,370
Did you see my daughter having an affair?

458
00:25:14,380 --> 00:25:15,940
Do you have any evidence?

459
00:25:15,940 --> 00:25:18,550
How dare you wag your finger

460
00:25:18,550 --> 00:25:20,110
at me in such a vulgar way?

461
00:25:20,110 --> 00:25:21,310
Vulgar way?

462
00:25:21,320 --> 00:25:23,280
Your name sounds very vulgar.

463
00:25:23,280 --> 00:25:24,520
So I can be vulgar to you.

464
00:25:24,520 --> 00:25:26,450
You're the one that's vulgar.

465
00:25:26,450 --> 00:25:28,790
Do you know that?

466
00:25:28,790 --> 00:25:32,060
I give her an inch and she takes a mile.

467
00:25:32,060 --> 00:25:34,160
Who do you think you are?

468
00:25:34,160 --> 00:25:36,530
Hey, newbie. Bae Chuja!

469
00:25:43,270 --> 00:25:45,110
Good shot!

470
00:25:45,110 --> 00:25:46,370
Let's take a break.

471
00:25:53,250 --> 00:25:55,180
Does your wife play golf, too?

472
00:25:56,380 --> 00:25:57,920
No.

473
00:25:57,920 --> 00:26:01,690
I told her to learn but she's good at such things.

474
00:26:01,690 --> 00:26:04,020
All she cares about is our son.

475
00:26:04,030 --> 00:26:07,160
She's always either at work or home.

476
00:26:10,970 --> 00:26:15,700
Wait, my wife came to my office earlier.

477
00:26:15,700 --> 00:26:16,640
Why?

478
00:26:16,640 --> 00:26:18,370
She asked me why I didn't

479
00:26:18,370 --> 00:26:20,140
tell her you were Grace Lee.

480
00:26:20,140 --> 00:26:21,410
I had forgotten all about it.

481
00:26:21,410 --> 00:26:24,240
So I was very surprised to hear her say it.

482
00:26:24,250 --> 00:26:27,080
I came up with an excuse.

483
00:26:27,080 --> 00:26:30,520
She such an innocent and good woman

484
00:26:30,520 --> 00:26:33,120
that I'm sure she'll just let it go.

485
00:26:33,120 --> 00:26:35,260
Innocent and good?

486
00:26:36,290 --> 00:26:38,560
Do you really think so?

487
00:26:39,560 --> 00:26:40,860
The way I see it,

488
00:26:40,860 --> 00:26:43,660
she's got you wrapped around her finger.

489
00:26:44,330 --> 00:26:45,670
Lee Hwayeong.

490
00:26:46,600 --> 00:26:48,600
Don't say that about my wife.

491
00:26:48,600 --> 00:26:49,870
You don't know her.

492
00:27:06,120 --> 00:27:07,890
Oh, man!

493
00:27:07,890 --> 00:27:09,990
What's wrong with this club?

494
00:27:10,890 --> 00:27:14,960
That fool. That stupid loser.

495
00:27:16,200 --> 00:27:19,970
You've been fooled by Baek Yeonhui.

496
00:27:21,470 --> 00:27:23,070
Mom.

497
00:27:23,070 --> 00:27:26,410
Mom, will you do this for me?

498
00:27:26,410 --> 00:27:27,840
Do it yourself.

499
00:27:27,840 --> 00:27:29,280
Mom!

500
00:27:29,280 --> 00:27:30,680
Do it yourself.

501
00:27:30,680 --> 00:27:33,350
Mom, mom.

502
00:27:33,350 --> 00:27:35,620
Jeong Jinwu, what s wrong with you?

503
00:27:35,620 --> 00:27:37,520
Why are you whining?

504
00:27:37,520 --> 00:27:40,050
Didn't I tell you not to act like this?

505
00:27:42,890 --> 00:27:44,690
Jinwu, come here.

506
00:27:44,690 --> 00:27:46,260
I'll give you something yummy to eat.

507
00:27:46,260 --> 00:27:47,990
What's wrong?

508
00:27:48,000 --> 00:27:49,330
Grandma!

509
00:27:49,330 --> 00:27:53,370
Who yelled at my dear grandson?

510
00:27:53,370 --> 00:27:57,870
Who gave you the right to scold him?

511
00:27:57,870 --> 00:27:58,870
Mother.

512
00:27:58,870 --> 00:28:01,040
Jinwu keeps whining

513
00:28:01,040 --> 00:28:02,810
even over things he can do alone.

514
00:28:02,810 --> 00:28:04,480
Don't say that.

515
00:28:04,480 --> 00:28:06,410
He rarely gets a hug from you.

516
00:28:06,410 --> 00:28:08,450
So what if he whines a little?

517
00:28:08,450 --> 00:28:10,980
How can you be so cold?
You're his mother!

518
00:28:10,990 --> 00:28:13,420
Did you forget what we went through

519
00:28:13,420 --> 00:28:15,520
to have him?

520
00:28:15,520 --> 00:28:18,630
But mother, I should scold him if he deserves it.

521
00:28:18,630 --> 00:28:20,690
I'm afraid he'll end up being spoiled.

522
00:28:20,700 --> 00:28:22,030
Don't worry.

523
00:28:22,030 --> 00:28:25,200
Why worry about that already?

524
00:28:25,200 --> 00:28:27,570
You're such a worrywart.

525
00:28:29,440 --> 00:28:30,640
I'm home.

526
00:28:30,640 --> 00:28:32,370
Mom, I'm home.

527
00:28:32,370 --> 00:28:33,340
Dad!

528
00:28:33,340 --> 00:28:34,940
Come here, my boy!

529
00:28:36,240 --> 00:28:39,650
Jinwu, what about me?

530
00:28:39,650 --> 00:28:43,650
Say, "Auntie! Welcome home!"

531
00:28:43,650 --> 00:28:46,150
- No.
- Hey!

532
00:28:46,150 --> 00:28:48,560
Did you have a good day today, Jinwu?

533
00:28:49,420 --> 00:28:51,220
How come you're coming home together?

534
00:28:51,230 --> 00:28:53,430
Did you plan on coming home together?

535
00:28:53,430 --> 00:28:54,590
Not at all.

536
00:28:54,600 --> 00:28:56,830
Usually, it's hard to see each other at home.

537
00:28:56,830 --> 00:28:59,270
But we met at the door by chance today.

538
00:28:59,270 --> 00:29:00,800
Did you have dinner?

539
00:29:00,800 --> 00:29:02,540
- Yes.
- Not me.

540
00:29:02,540 --> 00:29:04,570
I'm sorry but can you fix me something?

541
00:29:04,570 --> 00:29:06,010
I'll wash up.

542
00:29:06,010 --> 00:29:08,010
Jinwu, you can come hang out with me.

543
00:29:08,010 --> 00:29:09,210
Let's go.

544
00:29:11,910 --> 00:29:13,210
Jinsuk.

545
00:29:13,210 --> 00:29:16,350
Doesn't Byeongguk look worn out these days?

546
00:29:17,520 --> 00:29:19,620
It's because of that Grace Lee woman.

547
00:29:19,620 --> 00:29:22,960
She's done that to my precious son.

548
00:29:22,960 --> 00:29:27,030
I hope that the deal is finalized soon.

549
00:29:27,030 --> 00:29:31,600
Yeonhui, your mother hasn't been
getting us Oriental medicine lately.

550
00:29:31,600 --> 00:29:33,430
In the past,

551
00:29:33,430 --> 00:29:36,640
she used to bring us some every month.

552
00:29:37,940 --> 00:29:41,510
But after Jinwu was born, that ended.

553
00:29:41,510 --> 00:29:43,640
I'll ask my mother about it.

554
00:29:43,640 --> 00:29:46,380
It's not because I don't want
to buy it myself.

555
00:29:46,380 --> 00:29:47,850
Mothers-in-law are supposed

556
00:29:47,850 --> 00:29:49,420
to be like mothers, too.

557
00:29:50,820 --> 00:29:52,850
Get your husband some tea

558
00:29:52,850 --> 00:29:55,160
so he can unwind a bit.

559
00:29:55,890 --> 00:29:56,920
Okay.

560
00:29:59,790 --> 00:30:02,930
Why is she so down?

561
00:30:02,930 --> 00:30:04,660
What's wrong with her?

562
00:30:04,670 --> 00:30:06,370
Come on.

563
00:30:06,370 --> 00:30:08,000
Okay, okay.

564
00:30:08,000 --> 00:30:10,270
How many times must I tell you

565
00:30:10,270 --> 00:30:12,410
that people like Yeonhui are hard to come by.

566
00:30:12,410 --> 00:30:14,940
She never complains.

567
00:30:14,940 --> 00:30:17,480
Nor does she say she wants to move out.

568
00:30:17,480 --> 00:30:20,450
She grew up like a princess

569
00:30:20,450 --> 00:30:23,050
but she doesn't ask us to treat her like one.

570
00:30:23,050 --> 00:30:24,720
Fine.

571
00:30:25,450 --> 00:30:27,420
Her looks, family and educational background.

572
00:30:27,420 --> 00:30:29,290
They can't be beat.

573
00:30:29,290 --> 00:30:32,030
I said I get it. You can stop now.

574
00:30:34,230 --> 00:30:37,300
But you know what?

575
00:30:37,300 --> 00:30:40,670
There's nothing I lack either.

576
00:30:40,670 --> 00:30:43,600
So why can't I get married?

577
00:30:57,180 --> 00:30:59,690
I'm really tired.

578
00:30:59,690 --> 00:31:02,220
Did you come home early?

579
00:31:02,220 --> 00:31:03,360
Yes.

580
00:31:04,860 --> 00:31:07,190
Come to think of it.

581
00:31:07,190 --> 00:31:10,930
I think I was too hard on you earlier

582
00:31:11,600 --> 00:31:14,130
when you came to see me at my office.

583
00:31:14,140 --> 00:31:15,970
You may be an owner of a coffee shop

584
00:31:15,970 --> 00:31:18,570
but I should've offered you a drink.

585
00:31:22,340 --> 00:31:24,480
It's okay. I'll do it.

586
00:31:27,280 --> 00:31:30,050
Oh, my little Jinwu.

587
00:31:30,050 --> 00:31:31,280
Let's go.

588
00:31:46,830 --> 00:31:49,670
<i>Grace Lee</i>

589
00:31:56,580 --> 00:31:58,580
What are you doing?

590
00:31:58,580 --> 00:32:00,850
What are you doing with my phone?

591
00:32:00,850 --> 00:32:02,620
It was ringing.

592
00:32:02,620 --> 00:32:03,750
You've been acting strange lately.

593
00:32:03,750 --> 00:32:05,950
You never used to act like this before.

594
00:32:06,850 --> 00:32:08,860
It's not that.

595
00:32:08,860 --> 00:32:10,420
It's Grace Lee.

596
00:32:11,260 --> 00:32:15,260
Why is she calling me at this hour?

597
00:32:15,260 --> 00:32:17,760
Why didn't you tell me

598
00:32:17,770 --> 00:32:19,570
that you knew Grace Lee?

599
00:32:19,570 --> 00:32:22,770
That again? How is that important?

600
00:32:22,770 --> 00:32:23,870
It's strange.

601
00:32:23,870 --> 00:32:27,040
What? What's strange?

602
00:32:27,040 --> 00:32:29,010
It wasn't important.

603
00:32:29,010 --> 00:32:30,280
It's true.

604
00:32:30,280 --> 00:32:32,280
You have your own work.

605
00:32:32,280 --> 00:32:33,480
In the same way,

606
00:32:33,480 --> 00:32:36,150
I have my work with Grace Lee.

607
00:32:36,150 --> 00:32:39,390
If I told you about our business relationship,

608
00:32:39,390 --> 00:32:42,220
would you have been able to befriend her?

609
00:32:42,220 --> 00:32:44,160
It'd be awkward for all of us.

610
00:32:44,690 --> 00:32:47,190
I was only trying to be considerate.

611
00:32:47,190 --> 00:32:49,460
So why are suspecting me like this?

612
00:32:51,070 --> 00:32:54,000
Are you really suspicious of me?

613
00:32:55,200 --> 00:32:57,270
Is that it?

614
00:32:57,270 --> 00:32:58,610
You don't trust me?

615
00:32:59,110 --> 00:33:01,470
No, I don't trust you.

616
00:33:01,480 --> 00:33:02,610
Honey.

617
00:33:02,610 --> 00:33:04,440
Hwayeong and I have been close.

618
00:33:04,450 --> 00:33:06,650
But the two of you acted as if you

619
00:33:06,650 --> 00:33:08,580
met for the first time. Does that make sense?

620
00:33:08,580 --> 00:33:09,880
And if it doesn't?

621
00:33:09,880 --> 00:33:12,250
Are you saying I'm having an affair

622
00:33:12,250 --> 00:33:13,720
behind your back or something?

623
00:33:13,720 --> 00:33:16,360
That really doesn't make sense.

624
00:33:17,060 --> 00:33:20,260
I thought you were pure and good.

625
00:33:20,260 --> 00:33:22,500
Why are you acting like this?

626
00:33:22,500 --> 00:33:24,960
You don't trust me?

627
00:33:24,970 --> 00:33:27,000
What did I do wrong?

628
00:33:27,000 --> 00:33:28,330
This is so funny.

629
00:33:30,080 --> 00:33:30,990
Wait.

630
00:33:31,070 --> 00:33:33,140
Turn that down.

631
00:33:34,410 --> 00:33:35,510
Why?

632
00:33:36,280 --> 00:33:37,930
Don't make me out to be the bad guy.

633
00:33:38,180 --> 00:33:40,420
Why are you treating me like a fool?

634
00:33:40,750 --> 00:33:42,850
What's going on?

635
00:33:56,700 --> 00:33:59,770
What are you two doing?

636
00:34:40,070 --> 00:34:43,280
See you next time...

